	<pb facs="liv_020021_00001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend="center"><add place="inline" hand="#U" rend="gray">47</add></p>			    
<lb/><p>I have heard that the <term type="tribe">Boers</term> say <persName>Livingstone</persName>
<lb/>sold me guns. <choice><sic>they</sic><corr>They</corr></choice> tell falsehoods. <choice><sic>he</sic><corr>He</corr></choice> never sold
<lb/>me any nor yet lent me any.
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><add place="inline" hand="#S" n="signature1 liv_020021_00001"><persName>Secele</persName></add>
<lb/>
<lb/>I was never under <persName>Mosilikatse</persName>'s rule. <choice><sic>he</sic><corr>He</corr></choice> made
<lb/>war upon and beat me but I did not submit
<lb/>to him. I went to the <region>Kalagare</region> where he was
<lb/>not able to follow me</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="words"/>The <term type="collective">Boers</term> also say that
<lb/><choice><sic>that</sic><corr></corr></choice> I became their servant and thay I made
<lb/>a treaty with them. I never made a treaty 
<lb/>with them nor yet submited to be ruled
<lb/>by them. The only instance in <choice><sic>wich</sic><corr>which</corr></choice> I requested
<lb/>their assistance was when the <term type="collective"><orig>Matabele</orig><reg>Ndebele</reg></term>
<lb/>attacked me at <settlement>Shokwane</settlement>. <choice><sic>this</sic><corr>This</corr></choice> they
<lb/>refused saying the <term type="collective"><orig>Matabele</orig><reg>Ndebele</reg></term> have <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">attacked</add> you
<lb/>and not us. This was long after the <term type="collective"><orig>Matabele</orig><reg>Ndebele</reg></term>
<lb/>had been driven out of the country by
<lb/><persName>Dingaan</persName>. When they attacked me they
<lb/>were on their way to attack <persName>Sebegue</persName> who had
<lb/>not long before returned from the <region><orig>Kalagare</orig><reg>Kalahari</reg></region>
<lb/>wither he had fled a long while before with
<lb/>all his people and cattle to escape <persName>Mosilikatse</persName>
<lb/><persName><choice><orig>Mosilikatse</orig><reg>Mzilikazi</reg></choice></persName> hearing of his return had sent an army
<lb/>against him</p>
<lb/><p>Translated from <persName>Sechele</persName>'s statement <add place="inline" hand="#S" n="signature2 liv_020021_00001"><persName>Secele</persName></add>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>by me in his presence <space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName>Samuel Edwards</persName>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><settlement>Cape Town</settlement> <date when="1853-05-07">May 7.<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date>.</p>
            
	<pb facs="liv_020021_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent" n="statement1 liv_020021_0002">Statements made by
<lb/>the <term type="collective"><choice><orig>Bakwain</orig><reg>Bakwena</reg></choice></term> chief
<lb/><persName>Sechele</persName>, in <settlement>Cape
<lb/>Town</settlement>, <date when="1853-05-07">7<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May 1853</date>,
<lb/>and confirmed by him,
<lb/>on the <date when="1853-05-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May 1853</date>,
<lb/>in the presence of
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName>Tom Thomson</persName>,
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><seg rend="italic"><persName>Samuel Edwards</persName></seg></p>

<lb/><p rend="italic no-indent">I have to the best of my ability translated to <persName>Sechele</persName>
<lb/>the Chief of the <term type="collective"><choice><orig>Bakwaina</orig><reg>Bakwena</reg></choice></term> the above paper from
<lb/>the <settlement>Cape Town</settlement> Mail of <date when="1853-04-26">26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April 1853</date> entitled "The
<lb/>Story of the Black Pot" alias. "The Story of Selling
<lb/>the Gun" and he affirms the statement it contains
<lb/>to be correct.
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="words"/><persName>Samuel Edwards</persName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="inline">The above statement, <persName>Mr Edwards</persName> acting as Interpreter, was
<lb/>confirmed in my presence - 
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName>Tom Thompson</persName>-
<lb/><date when="1853-05-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> 1853</date>-</add></p>

<lb/><p>The statement made by <persName>Sechele</persName> with reference to the attack,
<lb/>upon him by the <term type="collective">Boers</term>, and published in the "<settlement>Cape Town</settlement> Mail"
<lb/>a copy of which is appended, is confirmed this day, <date when="1853-05-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May
<lb/>1853</date>, <persName>Mr Edwards</persName> acting as Interpreter, in my presence.
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/><persName>Tom Thompson</persName>-
<lb/>
<lb/><seg n="metamark liv_020021_0002"><settlement>Cape Town</settlement>
<lb/><date when="1853-05-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May 1853</date>.</seg></p>
<lb/><space dim="vertical" unit="lines" extent="5"/>
